article.description: — Kasen Harrison had 18 points as Lamar easily defeated Incarnate Word 67-45 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Harrison scores 18 to carry Lamar past Incarnate Word 67-45
article.linkText: Harrison scores 18 to carry Lamar past Incarnate Word 67-45
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Kasen Harrison had 18 points as Lamar easily defeated Incarnate Word 67-45 on Wednesday night. Anderson Kopp had 14 points for Lamar (5-17, 4-10 Southland Conference), which snapped its six-game losing streak. Ellis Jefferson added 12 points. David Muoka had six points, 10 rebounds and four blocks. Keaston Willis had 15 points for UIW (8-10, 5-6). Lamar leveled the season series against UIW. UIW defeated Lamar 67-58 on Feb. 3. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
